locality: Serra do Cipó. About 23-24 km from the bridge over the Rio Cipó on the road from Serra do Cipó (formerly Cardeal Mota), about 38 km S of Conceição do Mato Dentro on a temporary detour road while the main Serra do Cipó/Conceição road was being paved.
occurrenceRemarks: Little-branched shrub to 1m tall. Leaves imbricate, 4-ranked. Flowers 5-merous. Petals pink with greenish-yellow patch at the base. Filaments, style, and pedoconnective yellow-green. Large anthers yellow turning brown. Small anthers yellow-orange. photo. Few plants seen growing with L. caryophyllea, L. grandulifera, L. firmula, and L. imbricata.
